    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min \u2013 these are your <strong>smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> into rings (discard the seeds and pith)</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 10 min, remove the tray from the oven and move the <strong>smoky potatoes</strong> to one side of the baking tray</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper rings </strong>and <strong>red onion wedges</strong> to the other side of the tray with a with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use a separate tray!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 15 min or or until everything is golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> mince</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong> in a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands are the best way!)</p><p>Divide and shape into equal-sized patties (1 per person!) \u2013 this is your <strong>burger patty[ies]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>garlic aioli</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad, </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half (if required!)</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and charred</p><p>Set aside until serving, reserving the pan</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>burger patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies] </strong>and reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese </strong>and cook, covered, for 5 min further until cooked through and charred (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy burger patty[ies]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-pork-and-beef-burger-with-potatoes-and-garlic-aioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, add a handful of <strong>salad </strong>to the <strong>toasted brioche base </strong>and top with some of the <strong>roasted pepper & onion</strong>, a <strong>cheesy burger patty</strong>, a spoonful of <strong>garlic aioli</strong> and the <strong>toasted brioche lid </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>Spanish-style burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>Spanish-style burger</strong> with the <strong>smoky potatoes</strong>, <strong>remaining salad</strong>, <strong>roasted pepper & onion </strong>and <strong>garlic aioli </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
